PRE-STEAM TECHNICAL CHECKLIST
================================================================================
Everything required before the app is ready for Steam distribution.
Steam distributes through the Steam client so Windows code signing is not
required. macOS Gatekeeper signing is also deferred — Windows-first release.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BLOCKING — App cannot ship without these
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[ ] Steamworks Developer Account + App ID
    - Register at partner.steamgames.com ($100 one-time fee)
    - Create the app listing to receive a Steam App ID
    - Add steam_appid.txt to the project root containing only the App ID
    - Required before any Steam features (achievements, cloud saves) can be
      tested, and before the store page can go live

[ ] Windows Build Verification via GitHub Actions CI
    - better-sqlite3 is a native Node module that must compile per-platform
    - No CI currently exists (.github/workflows/ folder is missing)
    - Create a workflow that:
        1. Checks out the repo on windows-latest runner
        2. Runs npm ci
        3. Runs npm test (Vitest suite)
        4. Runs npm run make to produce a packaged .exe
        5. Uploads the artifact for QA download
    - This must pass cleanly before any build is submitted to Steam

[ ] App Icon (.ico and .icns)
    - forge.config.ts packagerConfig has no icon field
    - Without it the app shows a generic Electron icon on Windows and macOS
    - Create assets/icon.ico (256×256 minimum, multi-size preferred)
    - Create assets/icon.icns (macOS, 512×512)
    - Add to forge.config.ts: icon: './assets/icon'
    - The icon is also required for the Steam store capsule artwork

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HIGH PRIORITY — Will hurt reviews or crash reports if shipped as-is
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[ ] Content Security Policy (index.html)
    - src/index.html has no CSP meta tag
    - Electron logs security warnings on every launch without it
    - Add to <head>:
      <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"
        content="default-src 'self'; script-src 'self';
                 style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'">

[ ] win32metadata in forge.config.ts
    - MakerSquirrel config is empty ({})
    - Windows Add/Remove Programs and .exe properties show blank fields
    - Add to MakerSquirrel config:
        name: 'GridironDynasty'
        authors: 'Blake Whitney'
        description: 'A professional football dynasty simulator'
        iconUrl: (URL to hosted .ico)
        setupIcon: './assets/icon.ico'

[ ] productName and appCategoryType in packagerConfig
    - forge.config.ts packagerConfig is missing:
        executableName: 'GridironDynasty'        (no spaces — required on Linux)
        appCopyright: 'Copyright 2026 Blake Whitney'
        appCategoryType: 'public.app-category.games'   (macOS App Store category)

[ ] Error Boundary (React)
    - No ErrorBoundary component wraps <App />
    - Any unhandled JS error in any tab causes a full blank white screen crash
    - Add a top-level ErrorBoundary class component in src/ErrorBoundary.tsx
      that catches render errors and shows a styled fallback UI with a
      "Restart App" button calling window.api.reloadApp() or ipcRenderer
      invoke('reload')
    - Wrap <App /> in renderer.ts with <ErrorBoundary>

[ ] Main Process Crash Logging
    - No uncaughtException or unhandledRejection handlers in src/index.ts
    - When the main process crashes, there is no log and no user feedback
    - Add to index.ts:
        process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => {
          fs.appendFileSync(path.join(app.getPath('userData'), 'crash.log'),
            `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${err.stack}\n`);
        });
        process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason) => {
          fs.appendFileSync(path.join(app.getPath('userData'), 'crash.log'),
            `[${new Date().toISOString()}] ${String(reason)}\n`);
        });
    - Writes crash.log to the userData folder (same place as save files)

[ ] Remove Unused Dependencies
    - package.json contains two unused packages alongside better-sqlite3:
        "better": "^0.1.0"      — unrelated package, adds noise
        "sqlite3": "^6.0.1"     — duplicate; only better-sqlite3 is used
    - Remove both from dependencies to reduce bundle size and eliminate
      potential native compile failures on Windows during CI

[ ] squirrel-startup Guard in index.ts
    - electron-squirrel-startup is in dependencies but its guard call
      must be the very first line of src/index.ts to prevent the app
      from launching multiple instances during Windows install/uninstall
    - Verify or add at the top of index.ts:
        import started from 'electron-squirrel-startup';
        if (started) app.quit();

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MEDIUM PRIORITY — Expected polish for a Steam release
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[ ] Minimum Window Size Enforcement
    - BrowserWindow is created at 1200×700 with no minWidth/minHeight
    - Users can resize the window smaller than the UI is designed for,
      breaking layout
    - Add to createWindow(): minWidth: 1100, minHeight: 650

[ ] Prevent Multiple App Instances
    - No single-instance lock in index.ts
    - A user double-clicking the app while it's running opens a second window
    - Add: const lock = app.requestSingleInstanceLock();
            if (!lock) { app.quit(); return; }
            app.on('second-instance', () => { mainWindow?.focus(); });

[ ] Renderer Error Logging
    - No window.onerror or window.onunhandledrejection handler in renderer.ts
    - JS errors in the renderer process are silently swallowed in production
    - Add to renderer.ts:
        window.onerror = (msg, src, line, col, err) => {
          console.error('Renderer error:', msg, src, line, col, err);
        };
        window.onunhandledrejection = (e) => {
          console.error('Unhandled promise rejection:', e.reason);
        };

[ ] Loading / Splash Screen
    - BrowserWindow starts with show: false and reveals on ready-to-show
      which is correct, but there is no branded splash while the app loads
    - For a Steam release, a brief branded loading screen before the main
      menu significantly improves first-impression feel

[ ] Keyboard Shortcut Cleanup
    - Default Electron menu is removed (Menu.setApplicationMenu(null))
      which is correct, but Ctrl+R (reload) and F5 still work in production
      builds via webContents defaults
    - Register a globalShortcut to disable Ctrl+R and F5 in production:
        app.on('ready', () => {
          if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'development') {
            globalShortcut.register('Control+R', () => {});
            globalShortcut.register('F5', () => {});
          }
        });

